               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-251-person2189">
                  JAMES 
                  SWAIN
               <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2189" type="surname" value="SWAIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2189" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2189" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am errand-boy to Mr. Woollard. On the 12th of April, between seven and eight o'clock, I saw the prisoner take a table from outside Mr. Goode's shop, opposite the window; I gave an alarm - he put it down at the corner of Crown-street, and ran off; there was a cry of Stop thief! and he was taken in five or ten minutes - I lost sight of him as he turned Charles-street, Pitfield-street; I am sure he is the person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-251-person2190">
                  ELIZABETH 
                  ALLEN
               <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2190" type="surname" value="ALLEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2190" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2190" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I lodge at Mr. 
               <persName id="t18300415-251-person2191">
                  Thomas 
                  Goode
               <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2191" type="surname" value="Goode"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2191" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2191" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's, in <placeName id="t18300415-251-crimeloc1394">Old Street-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-251-crimeloc1394" type="placeName" value="Old Street-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-251-crimeloc1394" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-251-off1392 t18300415-251-crimeloc1394"></join>. This table was near his shop-door - the witness ran up stairs to me; as I came down the table was brought into the shop by an errand-boy; I went round the corner to look for my husband, and picked up the prisoner's hat - this is the table.</p>
               <p>JAMES SWAINE. As the prisoner was putting his head under the table, his hat fell off.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-251-person2192">
                  JOSEPH 
                  ELISHES
               <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2192" type="surname" value="ELISHES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2192" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2192" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am errand-boy to Mr. Goode. I saw the prisoner put the table down at the corner of Crown-street; I had not seen him take it up - I called out Stop thief! I did not see him caught, but saw him immediately afterwards - he dropped his hat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-251-person2193">
                  JOHN 
                  JOHNSON
               <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2193" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2193" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-251-person2193" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in conversation with a friend, at the corner of Crown-street; I saw a man coming with a table on his shoulder - there was a cry of Stop thief! he<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183004150120"></xptr>put it down and ran off - my friend pursued him; he was without a hat.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A man rushed round the corner and took off my hat - I ran after him, and a man gave charge of me.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 25.</p>
